# Appointment Test Cases

This document lists key manual test cases for the Online Appointment System.  
Each case includes preconditions, steps and the expected result. See the Excel file for full details.

## Scope
- Authentication (login)
- Appointment booking, reschedule, cancellation
- Notifications (email/SMS)
- Provider availability
- Security monitoring (basic alert)

## Sample Cases
- **TC-LOGIN-001** – Login with valid credentials → user lands on dashboard, session created.  
- **TC-LOGIN-002** – Invalid password → error message, no session.  
- **TC-BOOK-001** – Book available slot → booking saved, confirmation shown.  
- **TC-BOOK-002** – Prevent double booking → conflict message.  
- **TC-BOOK-003** – Reschedule to a different slot → time updated, provider schedule refreshed.  
- **TC-BOOK-004** – Cancel ≥2h before start → booking removed, slot opens, notification sent.  
- **TC-BOOK-005** – Block cancellation <2h → policy message shown.  
- **TC-NOTIF-001** – Confirmation email/SMS sent after booking/reschedule.  
- **TC-PROV-001** – Provider sets working hours → only in-range slots visible.  
- **TC-SEC-001** – Suspicious IP triggers alert → access blocked/challenged, alert logged.

*For full steps and preconditions, refer to the Excel sheet.*